message.content: Some of the biggest challenges teenagers in Italy face include educational pressure and competitiveness, limited employment opportunities and job insecurity, substance abuse and addiction, mental health issues such as anxiety and depression, bullying and peer pressure, social media addiction and cyberbullying, economic inequality, and political disillusionment. Additionally, they may also struggle with balancing academic responsibilities with extracurricular activities and peer relationships, as well as grappling with the pressure to conform to societal expectations and cultural norms.
